Introduction
This package contains the default installation scenarios for initially setting up a new GoldenSource system. It is a workbench feature for the GoldenSource Workbench and needs to be installed as described below.

Installation Instructions

To install directly from the GoldenSource Download Site you must:

  1. Start GoldenSource Workbench
  2. New Features/Updates link on the welcome page or choose Help / Software Updates / Find and install... from the menu. The Install/Update wizard opens.
  3. If Installation Center is already installed in a previous version, choose Search for updates of the currently installed features and press [Finish]. If Installation Center has not been installed yet, choose Search for new features to install. The Update Site to Visit page appears. Select GoldenSource Download Site and press [Finish].
  4. You will be asked for user credentials to login to GoldenSource Download Site.
  5. The available features are presented on the Search Results page. If you cannot find your desired version, try to deselect checkbox Show the latest version of a feature only. Select the plug-ins you want to install and press [Next].
  6. Accept the license agreement and press [Next].
  7. Press [Finish] to start the installation.
  8. You can safely ignore the verification message about the feature not being digitally signed -just press the [Install All] button.
  9. After the features have been installed you are prompted to restart. Press [Yes] to restart.

To install from the package zip file you must:

  1. Start GoldenSource Workbench
  2. Click the New Features/Updates link on the welcome page or choose Help / Software Updates / Find and install... from the menu. The Install/Update wizard opens.
  3. Select the Search for new features to install option and press [Next]. The Update Site to Visit page appears.
  4. Click [New Archived Site…] and specify the file package zip file.
  5. Click [Finish] to start searching the archive file for features to install.
  6. The available features are presented on the Search Results page. Select the plug-ins you want to install and press [Next]:
  7. Accept the license agreement and press [Next].
  8. Press [Finish] to start the installation.
  9. You can safely ignore the verification message about the feature not being digitally signed -just press the [Install All] button.
  10. After the features have been installed you are prompted to restart. Press [Yes] to restart.

Installation Verification
From GoldenSource Installation Center choose Help / About GoldenSource Workbench and click on the [Feature Details] button. Verify that the Installation Center version displayed is correct.
